The measurement of 2,2′-azinobis-3-ethylbenzothiazoline-6-sulfonic acid (ABTS) (Sigma-Aldrich, Germany) radical scavenging was carried out according to the protocol of Rufino et al. (2010)47 with some modifications. The ABTS radical solution was prepared by mixing 7.0 mmol/L ABTS and 2.5 mmol/L of potassium persulfate. Extracts of 10 μL were subsequently mixed with 290 μL of ABTS radical solution, and the absorbance of the resulting mixtures was measured after 30 min at 735 nm using Infinite 200 PRO NanoQuant reader (Tecan, Männedorf, Switzerland). The free radical-scavenging capacity was calculated by the following Equation (5):5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
